						<summary>

						<p>On the pillar set up in the courtyard of the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya, 1527 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1449, Sarvajit, Nija Āshāḍha ba. 30, Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1527 A.D., July 28, °29.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 1 <hi rend="italic">varāha-gadya</hi> per annum derived as <hi rend="italic">tēgam (tyāgam)</hi> due to them from the <hi rend="italic">kāṁpus</hi> to god Chennakēśava of Koṟṟapāḍu in Gaṇḍikōṭa-sīma, by Mīsaragaṇḍa Mādhavarāju and Kāki Kēśvarāju.</p>						

						</summary>
